  "bio_raw": "Foysal Ahmed is currently serving as a Lecturer in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering (CSE) at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh. He received his B.Sc. in CSE from BRAC University and later completed his M.Sc. in Software Engineering from the Institute of Information Technology, University of Dhaka.\nHis primary research interests include low-resource Natural Language Processing (NLP), with a particular focus on Bangla NLP. Beyond NLP, he is interested in machine learning techniques and software quality maintenance.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Natural Language Processing, Machine Learning, Software Engineering."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMSc in Software Engineering\n, Institute of Information Technology, University of Dhaka, November 2025.\nThesis: Context-Aware Bengali Sentence Validation and Grammatical Error Type Detection\nBSc in Computer Science and Engineering\n, BRAC University, March 2023\nThesis: Bangla Grammar and Spelling Check Using Machine Learning"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journals Article\nFoysal Ahmed\n, Md. Abdur Rahman, Sumon Ahmed. “Grammatical Error Correction in Low-Resource Languages: A Systematic Literature Review”. IAENG International Journal of Computer Science, 2026 [Accepted].",
